<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="62" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="62" type="mainText">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Anapidae" genus="Comaroma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">COMAROMA</taxonomicName>
Bertkau Figures 292-294
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="62" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="62" type="mainText">
Carapace as in 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Steatoda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Steatoda</taxonomicName>
, but heavily sclerotized. Six eyes, or if eight, then diameter of anterior medians less than radius of posterior eyes. Chelicerae strong with three anterior teeth and posterior denticles. First and fourth legs subequal. First patellatibia slightly short er than carapace. Tarsus slightly longer than metatarsus. Abdomen very heavliy sclerotized. Large colulus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="62" type="mainText">Small size, less than 1.5 mm total length.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="62" type="mainText">Epigynum with openings indistinct. Palpus with paracymbium on rim of cymbium, median apophysis reduced in size and not functional in holding bulb against cymbium; embolus of complex shape (Fig. 294).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="63" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="63" type="mainText">
<pageBreakToken pageId="1" pageNumber="63" start="start">Separated</pageBreakToken>
from 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Phoroncidia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Phoroncidia</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Pholcomma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pholcomma</taxonomicName>
by large colulus, from 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Robertus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Robertus</taxonomicName>
by heavy selerotization of abdomen and reduced anterior median eyes. This genus may be close to 
<taxonomicName family="Symphytognathidae" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" rank="family">Symphytognathidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="63" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="63" type="mainText">Two species known from southeastern Europe, one from California and one or two from Japan.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="63" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="63" type="mainText">
<taxonomicName authority="Levi, 1957" authorityName="Levi" authorityYear="1957" class="Arachnida" family="Anapidae" genus="Archerius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mendocino">
Archerius mendocino 
<authority pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Levi</authority>
</taxonomicName>
(from California) differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bertkau" class="Arachnida" family="Anapidae" genus="Comaroma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simoni">
Comaroma simoni 
<authority pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Bertkau</authority>
</taxonomicName>
(found in Europe) in being smaller and in details of the genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
